The paper deals with the storage and indexing of spatio-temporal data, which is a common topic in database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of a grammar-based compressor and the focus on efficient queries suggest a connection to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of quadtree structures and spatial range queries suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG).
